misconceptions.student_thought_process: The student believes they should read three floating-point inputs (v0, v1, t), compute the difference in velocities, divide by time, and print the result.
misconceptions.conceptual_gap: No conceptual gap detected: Java evaluates expressions left-to-right with correct operator precedence; storing intermediate results (a = v1 - v0; b = a / t) correctly implements a = (v1 - v0) / t. Using double avoids integer division issues.
misconceptions.error_manifestation: None for valid inputs (t != 0). Output matches the required computation and sample behavior.

evidence.code_snippet:
double b=a/t;
System.out.println("The average acceleration is "+b);
